gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Lakers 134, Wizards 131
gameRecap.excerpt: The Lakers defeated the Wizards, 134-131, in overtime. Anthony Davis recorded 40 points, 15 rebounds, and three blocks for the Lakers, with LeBron James adding 31 points, nine assists, and four rebounds in the victory. Jordan Poole tallied a season-high 34 points along with seven assists, and three rebounds for the Wizards in the losing effort. The Lakers improve to 33-28, while the Wizards fall to 9-50.
